decks.notes: This Jeskai Aggro deck focuses on quickly setting up a board of aggressive creatures and disrupting the opponent with removal spells and control elements. The deck utilizes cards like Ajani, Guide of Souls and Ranger-Captain of Eos to efficiently flood the board with threats while using cards like Galvanic Discharge and Goblin Bombardment to remove opposing creatures. The inclusion of cards like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Static Prison adds a layer of disruption to slow down the opponent's game plan, allowing the deck to push for a quick and decisive victory.

This deck focuses on utilizing the combo potential of Underworld Breach and Grinding Station to mill the opponent's library and win the game. The deck includes various cards to support the combo, such as Mishra's Bauble, Mox Opal, and Emry, Lurker of the Loch, along with disruption spells like Swan Song and Unholy Heat. The inclusion of Urza's Saga and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps to generate extra value and card advantage. Overall, the deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure a victory.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on a high tempo strategy, utilizing cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Guide of Souls to quickly put pressure on the opponent. The deck also includes disruption elements like Static Prison and Thraben Charm to control the board. Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Fable of the Mirror-Breaker provide additional power and card advantage. The main win conditions are Goblin Bombardment and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, backed up by Ocelot Pride for additional threats. Showdown of the Skalds can provide a huge mana boost and card advantage in the mid to late game.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy with a variety of counterspells and removal spells, while also utilizing creatures with disruptive abilities. It aims to control the game by countering key spells, removing threats from the board, and out-valuing the opponent with card advantage. The deck also employs graveyard synergies to generate value and provide additional disruption. The mana base is designed to support the deck's multicolor requirements and ensure consistency in casting spells on curve.

The deck focuses on utilizing low-cost creatures and cards like Aether Vial to quickly build a board presence and disrupt your opponent's game plan. With cards like Ephemerate and Flickerwisp, the deck can generate value by repeatedly blinking key creatures. These creatures, such as Recruiter of the Guard and Guide of Souls, help assemble a synergistic lineup of creatures that can overwhelm the opponent. Additionally, the deck includes removal spells like Fatal Push and Solitude to disrupt opposing strategies. The goal is to outpace and outvalue the opponent while utilizing disruptive elements to control the game.

The deck focuses on using disruptive creatures and removal spells to control the board while also utilizing cards that allow for recursion or blinking of creatures. The goal is to put pressure on the opponent's resources and disrupt their game plan, while also being able to generate card advantage and maintain a strong board presence. The creatures in the deck are versatile and can be used aggressively or defensively as needed, making it a flexible and adaptive strategy. Additionally, the mana base is designed to support the deck's aggressive strategy while also providing the necessary colors for the various cards included.

This deck focuses on utilizing a combination of spells and creatures to quickly assemble a win condition without relying on traditional lands. By using cards like Disrupting Shoal and Force of Negation for control, and cards like Goblin Charbelcher and Thundertrap Trainer for damage, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with powerful combo plays. The key strategy is to manipulate the board state and mana resources efficiently to create a fast and flexible win condition that can catch opponents off guard.

The main idea of this deck is to quickly and aggressively build up your board presence with a combination of efficient creatures and removal spells, while also disrupting your opponent's game plan with hand disruption spells. By combining powerful creatures like Sheoldred, the Apocalypse and Emperor of Bones with cards like Fatal Push and Abrupt Decay, you aim to overwhelm your opponent and close out the game before they have a chance to stabilize. The inclusion of cards like Nihil Spellbomb and Dauthi Voidwalker also provide utility and disruption against certain strategies.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on fast, aggressive gameplay by using efficient creatures and burn spells to quickly diminish the opponent's life total. The deck includes powerful cards like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah, Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury, and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer to apply pressure early on. With cards like Goblin Bombardment and Galvanic Discharge for direct damage, along with control elements like Static Prison and Elegant Parlor, the deck aims to maintain board presence and pressure the opponent into a quick defeat.

This deck focuses on utilizing Eldrazi creatures to control the game and ramp up to powerful threats quickly. By using cards like Eldrazi Temple and Ugin's Labyrinth, the deck can quickly accelerate mana production and play big Eldrazi creatures like Emrakul, the Promised End and World Breaker. In addition, cards like Karn, the Great Creator can shut down opponents' strategies while also providing utility. The deck also includes Kozilek's Return and Kozilek's Command for additional control options, making it a versatile and powerful control deck with ramp capabilities.

The deck revolves around using Grinding Station and Emry, Lurker of the Loch to repeatedly mill cards from the library and generate mana with Mox Opal and Mox Amber. Underworld Breach allows for recursion of key combo pieces while Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps dig for them. The goal is to eventually loop through the deck, generate a large amount of mana, and win the game with Thassa's Oracle or Malevolent Rumble. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Teferi, Time Raveler and removal spells to thwart opponent's strategies.

This Boros Aggro deck focuses on aggressive creature plays and burn spells to quickly deal damage to the opponent. The key strategy is to establish a board presence with efficient creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Seasoned Pyromancer, while also using burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Galvanic Discharge to control the board and finish off the opponent. The deck also utilizes cards like Guide of Souls and Ajani, Nacatl Pariah to buff its creatures and push through damage. Blood Moon is included to disrupt the opponent's mana base and gain an advantage.
